  { :title => "Delicious Food Cart Walking Tour", :description => "New York City's mobile food carts have moved from street meat to more haute cuisine, offering delicacies such as kati rolls, Jamaican jerk chicken and even tasty deserts. This two hour guided New York Food Tour will highlight the best of the new Food Cart bunch.\r\n\r\nYou and your guest will enjoy a strolling lunch around Midtown or Downtown Manhattan as you sample an international menu of offerings, observe the constructive genius that cram full kitchens into tiny carts, and discover the stories of their proprietors--from struggling immigrants to culinary school drop-outs, to former 4-star restaurant chefs. Along the way, your Guide will discuss the history of the challenges of running these demanding, yet delicious small businesses.  \r\n\r\nMouth-watering bites on the tour range from falafel and vegetables, chicken and rice with tamarind sauce, Korean short ribs, waffles with toppings, schnitzel, kati rolls, jerk or stewed chicken, to Mexican chocolate brownies! So whether you are looking for fun things to do in New York, a unique gift or a guide to the perfect New York City lunch, this NYC Food Cart Tour is the perfect experience gift!", :guide_id => nil, :created_at => "2012-05-19 21:45:04", :updated_at => "2012-05-20 04:24:58", :image_file_name => "food-truck.jpg", :image_content_type => "image/jpeg", :image_file_size => 50055, :image_updated_at => "2012-05-19 21:45:04", :banner_file_name => "china_banner.jpg", :banner_content_type => "image/jpeg", :banner_file_size => 521843, :banner_updated_at => "2012-05-20 01:27:54", :price => 70, :hours => 2 },
  { :title => "Chinatown Food and Culture Walking Tour", :description => "Discover the tasty secrets of the delicious cuisine and culture of New York City's Chinatown on this exciting three-hour Chinese Food and Culture Walking Tour in New York City. Your knowledgeable guide will lead you through this eclectic neighborhood, up and down the bustling, little streets of Downtown Manhattan and Chinatown, making several stops along the way to taste some of the most delicious foods that make this neighborhood so unique. So get ready to discover the art of dumplings, Peking Duck and more!\r\n\r\nOn this Manhattan Culinary Tour you will also explore historic landmarks, as well as some outdoor markets located in this small district, home to the second largest concentration of Chinese Americans in the western hemisphere. During this New York Food Tour you will visit and sit-down at two of Chinatown's finest restaurants and enjoy regional Chinese cuisine, while observing the traditional etiquette that is partnered with these fine foods. After each stop you will continue on your Walking Tour, venturing through the neighborhood and stopping at one of a kind specialty food shops for additional tastings and cultural insight.", :guide_id => nil, :created_at => "2012-05-19 21:45:44", :updated_at => "2012-05-20 04:18:10", :image_file_name => "chinatown.jpg", :image_content_type => "image/jpeg", :image_file_size => 44546, :image_updated_at => "2012-05-19 21:45:44", :banner_file_name => "chinatown.JPG", :banner_content_type => "image/jpeg", :banner_file_size => 252668, :banner_updated_at => "2012-05-20 04:18:10", :price => 50, :hours => 1 },
  { :title => "Gospel Music Tour of Brooklyn", :description => "Gospel Music's roots in New York go back to the turn of the century, when former slaves migrated to the North in search of work and freedom from racial oppression. The musical heritage has been passed down through the generations and today Brooklyn, known as the City of Churches, features some of the most uplifting Gospel Music in all of the five boroughs.  \r\n\r\nDuring this Tour of Brooklyn, you and your guest will discover the beautiful houses of worship and phenomenal music New York has to offer. Your knowledgeable and friendly Guide will provide background on the culture and history of Brooklyn churches prior to escorting you to a Sunday worship service where you will enjoy the soul-stirring power of gospel music from a Grammy Award Winning Gospel Choir.", :guide_id => nil, :created_at => "2012-05-19 21:46:00", :updated_at => "2012-05-20 04:13:54", :image_file_name => "gospel.jpg", :image_content_type => "image/jpeg", :image_file_size => 33593, :image_updated_at => "2012-05-19 21:46:00", :banner_file_name => "gospel.jpg", :banner_content_type => "image/jpeg", :banner_file_size => 150762, :banner_updated_at => "2012-05-20 04:13:39", :price => 90, :hours => 2 },
  { :title => "Crazy Awesome Graffiti Tour", :description => "The word graffiti comes from the Greek word 'graphein' which means 'to write'. Graffiti was first found on ancient Roman architecture, although back in them days there was no such thing as spray paint, they calved images out on walls.\r\n\r\nWant to see the street art world's heavy weights like Shepard Fairey? Want to see the The Phillie Phanatic wheatpasted on a wall? Experience the Magic Gardens first hand. Come learn about the dark world of gang art while also seeing one of New York's most famous tile artists. Discover the history of the New York Mural Arts Project (MAP) in a broader context. This tour covers the entire spectrum of street art New York has to offer!", :guide_id => nil, :created_at => "2012-05-19 21:46:22", :updated_at => "2012-05-20 04:14:19", :image_file_name => "graffiti.jpg", :image_content_type => "image/jpeg", :image_file_size => 60734, :image_updated_at => "2012-05-19 21:46:22", :banner_file_name => "new-york-graffiti.jpg", :banner_content_type => "image/jpeg", :banner_file_size => 958243, :banner_updated_at => "2012-05-20 03:41:39", :price => 60, :hours => 3 },
  { :title => "Harlem Soul Food Jazz Tour", :description => "Price for 2 participants Relive the high-stepping, fun-loving nights of the 1920’s on this Harlem Soul Food and Jazz Tour for two! Your Guide will teach you and your guest about Harlem's role in the history of Jazz music as you explore the famous land marks of this exciting New York neighborhood and savor some of the best Soul Food in Town!\r\n\r\nDuring this exciting Jazz Tour you will see the site of the original Cotton Club, check out the world-famous Apollo Theater, pass by Minton’s Playhouse and discover one of Harlem's hottest clubs. On the menu - dinner at Sylvia’s legendary restaurant The Queen of Soul Food. Monday evening tours offer swing dancing to a twelve-piece band while Thursday and Saturday evening tours offer the sounds of jazz or rhythm & blues.", :guide_id => nil, :created_at => "2012-05-19 21:46:36", :updated_at => "2012-05-20 04:21:46", :image_file_name => "jazz.jpg", :image_content_type => "image/jpeg", :image_file_size => 29501, :image_updated_at => "2012-05-19 21:46:36", :banner_file_name => "jazz.jpg", :banner_content_type => "image/jpeg", :banner_file_size => 120021, :banner_updated_at => "2012-05-20 04:21:46", :price => 270, :hours => 4 },
